Subject: Re: [PowerShell/PowerShell] Rid of TypeResolver.ResolveType() call from Process_Types_Ps1Xml() (PR #16349)


@daxian-dbw commented on this pull request.

________________________________

In src/System.Management.Automation/engine/SecurityDescriptorCommandsHelperBase.cs<https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/pull/16349#discussion_r742576427>:

> +                    Marshal.SizeOf(new uint());
+                bool ret = NativeMethods.IsValidSid(pSid);
+                if (!ret)
+                {
+                    throw new Win32Exception(Marshal.GetLastWin32Error());
+                }
+
+                return new SecurityIdentifier(pSid);
+            }
+            finally
+            {
+                NativeMethods.LocalFree(pSd);
+            }
+        }
+
+#if !CORECLR


The code shouldn't be removed. It was enclosed by CORECLR because the Win32 API LsaQueryCAPs was not available on NanoServer. Now it should be enabled in theory. I think we need @TravisEz13<https://github.com/TravisEz13> or @PaulHigin<https://github.com/PaulHigin> to take a look.

